                        {
                            "text": "Convert speech to text",
                            "type": "heading"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "In this section, you'll learn how to transcribe audio, whether it's dialogue or voiceover.",
                            "type": "text"
                        },
                        {
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Open the <$Text$> panel by choosing <$Window$> > <$Text$>."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Under the <$Captions$> tab, click <$Transcribe Sequence$> to start the process."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "The default settings in the <$Create Transcript$> dialog box should be fine, so click <$Transcribe$>."
                                },
                                {
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Success!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "Great job isolating a specific color in the clip and adjusting the level to perfect the shot and boost the colors. There are a lot of different curve tools available in the <$Lumetri Color$> panel that you can explore. Check them out before moving on to the next tutorial."
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "text": "After the transcription process ends, you'll see the text appear in the <$Transcript$> tab. Don't worry if you spot imperfections; you can edit those later."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Click <$Next$> when you're ready to move to the next section, where you'll add the captions you just created to the <$Timeline$> panel."
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "listSubsteps"
                        }
